From a7e10ef5fb3397b4d03f630dd839c980cf1394aa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 00:24:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Split Mission Control into Shop Floor Dashboard (passive)
 and Supervisor Dashboard (interactive)

Correction from the previous session: the Task Completed button never
belonged on Mission Control - that page's actual job is a live,
read-only status board meant to run on a shop-floor TV so everyone can
see what's happening, not something anyone clicks through to do work.

- Mission Control renamed to "Shop Floor Dashboard" at /shop-floor
  (old /mission-control now redirects there). All interactivity removed:
  no Task Completed button, no Start Entire Unit panel, filters hidden
  in TV mode. Added a real TV Mode toggle using the Fullscreen API on
  the page's own container - hides the sidebar/header (they're DOM
  siblings, not children, so fullscreen on this element excludes them)
  and scales up card/text size for viewing from a distance.
- Login and the "View As" redirect both now land on /shop-floor.
- Rebuilt /department-work as "Supervisor Dashboard" - this is where
  Task Completed and Start Entire Unit actually live now. Same
  department-locking as before (supervisors see only their assigned
  department, config:manage holders see all), same station-grouped
  card layout and TaskCard component as Shop Floor for visual
  consistency, but every card here has the working Task Completed
  button, with automatic fallback to the detail drawer if a task
  actually requires a checklist that isn't done yet.
- Admin's per-department sidebar shortcuts now point to /shop-floor
  (the read-only view makes more sense for an admin doing oversight
  across many departments than the action-oriented Supervisor
  Dashboard, which is built around one department at a time).
